body:
I Do, Do You?

This specific imagine goes out to @strcwberrywine who came up with this lovely idea ❤️. Enjoy it!

Warnings: PURE FLUFF, slight angst

Pairing: Harry Styles x Y/N

——

Y/N and Harry had been together over 4 years. They had known each other for ages— they weren’t best friends or anything, but they did see each other on occasion. Both his family and hers constantly bugged him about when he was going to propose; he just shrugged and laughed it off. “When you know, you know.” He said.

That made Y/N start to question their entire relationship.

When you know, you know? Seriously? What kind of response is that? She thought.

So one night she sat him down and decided to confront him about it.

“H, what is this?” Y/N asked one night as they were watching the telly. Harry’s neck snapped toward her, his eyes swimming with confusion.

“What do you mean, love?” He asked, grabbing her hand to pull her close, but Y/N stood her ground as she got off the couch to look down at him.

“I mean, what are we, Harry? We’ve been together over 4 years and it’s like you’ve not even thought about marriage! Every time one of our family members jokes or asks about where our relationship is going, you just shrug or say “when it happens, it happens” it’s bullshit! Are you having second thoughts? Do you not want me anymore?” Y/N cried.

H was horrified by her outburst and quickly stood to comfort her.

“Hey, hey, love. Listen to me,” he said, pulling her in for a hug. “You are the love of my life. There’s no one I’d rather spend the rest of my life with. To see you walking down the aisle toward me in the most perfect white dress, to see your tummy full of our babies, to travel more of the world with you than I already have, is my dream!” Harry assured her.

“Then why haven’t you asked me to marry you?!” She asked, still crying. Not tears of sadness as they once were, but happiness and love and confusion from his statement.

“Because I’m dumb, love. I just think that I was waiting for too many things to be perfect. You never hinted at any rings when we went to Tiffany or Cartier or Bvgari. I just didn’t think you were ready. I’m all in. Forever.” He smiled, kissing Y/N’s forehead, tears pricking at his eyes as he wiped away hers.

“So then marry me, H. I’m ready. I’m done school in a month. I’m meeting you in Australia right after. We’ll travel and see the world. We’ll just be engaged instead of dating. I love you, Harry Styles. I have for over 4 incredibly adventurous and interesting years. I would love nothing more than to provide you with the life and babies you deserve. So, Harry Edward Styles, would you do me the honour of becoming my husband?” Y/N asked, getting down on one knee. She had a ring ready. She had planned to give it to him when he finished his solo tour, as a gift, not as an engagement ring, but it would do.

“Yes, Y/N Y/M/N L/N. I will gladly marry you.” He responded, pulling her off of her knees and kissing her fiercely. “I’m still going to get you a ring though, love. We can both wear them.” He smiled.

Y/N laughed and jumped up into Harry’s arms.

“Don’t worry, your mom and Gem and I have had one picked out for months.” Y/N giggled.

“Oh, is that so? Then I guess dress shopping won’t be an issue. God, I’m so clueless!” He joked.

“It’s okay, baby. I still love you.” She replied, pecking his nose.

summary: Have you ever heard the phrase “Having something to share that should not be shared, is like having money burning a hole in...
caption:
Have you ever heard the phrase “Having something to share that should not be shared, is like having money burning a hole in their pockets.”?

Nothing feels better than “telling all” to a friend. Perhaps you’re recounting the most amazing first date ever, or describing what a fool you made of yourself at the bar, or revealing something you just found out that maybe you should not have. We use our friends as sounding boards for the big decisions and the small decisions in our lives. We trust them with our secrets because we know that they won’t tell a soul. Except when they do. So, can you really trust anybody?

When we enter into relationships, we have to realize that no matter how close we might be to another person, we cannot control anyone’s behavior but our own, but if you can´t trust a friend to keep your secret how do we expect others to do that as well? No one is safe, specially when false information is being leaked. You have no idea who it might of been, maybe a friend, maybe a enemy or maybe someone you hung out with for an hour. It is true what they say, keep your friends close and your enemies closer ,you never know who will stab you in the back.

Unveiledhollywood is a celebrity group based on secrets with a little bit of a twist. Each member gets to choose an individual in their life that will expose their secret in the gossip blog. The secret being exposed might not even be true. It might not even be an individual your celeb have been knowing for a while or maybe even know at all, the list of possible exposers is endless. That is exactly what the roleplay is about. Look through our links and join as your favorite celebrity to see how long your secret will be kept. We accept right away and are now looking for a co-admin.

summary: My Lights Stay Up, But Your City Sleeps
body:
My Lights Stay Up, But Your City Sleeps

by PearlyDewdrops

summary

Harry breaks into his own smile, scrunching his nose when he glances back up, meeting Louis’ eyes, his stiff posture loosening. They stare for a beat, Harry’s smile dwindling. “So… you’re okay with it? That it can’t go anywhere?”

Louis nods easily. “We’re on the same page. Promise.” He holds out his pinkie to prove it, mind hazy and giddy from alcohol. Harry’s dimples appear in each cheek as he holds out his own, their pinkies intertwining. “We’re just two people who like each other, have fun together, and who may or may not kiss and… stuff.” He grins, wild adrenaline pumping through to his fingertips.

Harry sinks his teeth into his bottom lip, lowering his flushed gaze to the floor.

“Just don’t go falling in love with me, and it’ll be fine,” Louis smirks.

Or Louis has trouble sleeping, Harry has a habit of wrapping himself around Louis during the nights, and a mutual agreement to engage in a fun and simple thing quickly turns into something perhaps not so fun, and certainly not simple.

summary: Ain't That A Kick In The Head!
body:
Ain’t That A Kick In The Head!

by lesbianharrie, wreckingtomlinson

summary

“Well.” Niall unlocks his phone. “It wasn’t getting the traction I wanted on Snapchat. So…I tweeted it.”

What.

“You tweeted it,” Harry states, nearing a state of brain dead. “To your ten thousand followers.”

Niall nods, handing Harry the phone. “You’re a meme, Harry.”

“I’m a what?”

“A meme. It’s like an internet—”

“I know what a fucking meme is, Niall! Why did you make me into one?”

Niall has the fucking balls to cackle at that while Harry looks at the mess his former friend created. Videos of him screaming at Tomlinson about Tide Pods and his ass are being quoted and combined with memes to a create a level of memeception Harry has never seen before. That isn’t even including the thousands of tweets of him falling up the stairs remixed with random Top 40 songs.

~

In which Harry’s a disaster gay who doesn’t know shit about soccer, Liam drinks too many blue raspberry Coolattas, Niall knows everyone, Zayn looks dead, and Louis is Not Happy about sharing his breakout moment with “Drunk Hawaiian Guy.”
